Abstract:
KL Connect is a web-based campus notice board platform developed specifically for KL University, Bachupalli campus. The platform addresses a critical communication gap in college campuses where important announcements, exam schedules, events, and holidays are scattered across multiple WhatsApp groups and Telegram channels, leading to missed information and administrative inefficiency.
The system provides a unified, role-based communication platform where authorized administrators including faculty, HODs, and department heads can publish notices directly to targeted student groups based on department and year. Students receive real-time announcements in a clean, structured feed without the noise of general messaging platforms.
The platform implements a dual-role architecture where administrators can compose and publish categorized announcements including general notices, events, exam alerts, and holiday notifications, while students access a personalized read-only feed filtered to their department. Key features include real-time post delivery using Supabase, category-based filtering, department and year-wise targeting, urgent alert flagging, notice archiving, search functionality, toast notifications, and a secure admin panel.
Built using HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, and Supabase as the backend, the system demonstrates practical application of frontend engineering concepts including authentication, role-based access control, real-time database integration, and responsive UI design. The platform has been designed with scalability in mind to support the entire KLH student population of over 4000 students across multiple campuses.
Keywords: Campus Communication, Notice Board, Role-Based Access, Real-Time Database, Supabase, Department Targeting, Admin Panel